I have one mildly used Smith and Wesson SD9VE. This is the second generation of the Sigma pistols S&W made and was later sued by Glock because it so closely copied the design of the Glock 9mms. 

Mine has 300 rounds down the barrel and is extremely clean inside and out. I have added the Apex Tactical trigger spring kit and Apex Tactical AEK polymer trigger. I have all original trigger parts as well as all original paperwork that came with the gun. I only have one magazine, I did not receive the second one when I purchased it. This has been a wildly reliable and accurate gun, and I only want to part with it so that I can pursue either an M&P or a Glock. I am getting into both 3 and 2 gun competition and need something that I can upgrade to the nines. 

No offence to any of the trades out there but I am really only interested in a well known 9mm (not interested in other calipers) pistol that can be upgraded and used for competition. I understand that my gun is on the low side of the value scale compared to some of the others but I can possibly add cash, gun accessories or certain hard to find rimfire ammo to the trade.

My cash price is FIRM at $350. If I don't get at least that much I'll just keep the gun and use it as is for competition until I get the funds for a competition base gun.

All laws followed PPP (which I keep) or CCW required and a bill of sale will be completed

title: For Sale:  WAR S&W Regulation Police Target w/box & acces
postcontent:
The Regulation Police model was a square butt version of the I-frame in .32 S&W Long and .38 S&W. They were serial numbered in the Hand Ejector series. 

The Regulation Police was introduced in 1917 with special grips that extend beyond the bottom of the grip frame and are fitted into a notched backstrap. The grip design was patented, and the date impressed on Regulation Police grips. The notched (or "rebated") frame is also used on many of the .22/32 Target models and some pre-war .22/32 Kit Guns. Round butt guns did not use the rebated frame,is one is even rarer than normal Regulation Police Targets in that it is a pre-war model, made in 1932. (A collector on the S&W forum tracks pre-war models in a database and said he is aware of only 32 of them.), 6” bbl., target sights (of course), factory grips in EXCELLENT condition with just a few scratches ,I REALLY wish I had the money to keep this baby.and  i am waiting for serious buyer

title: For Sale:  1980 hunting camper for sale or trade
postcontent:
Vintage camper history. This beauty was created here in Indiana. It sits on a GMC Vandura35 Chassis and has a GMC 400 small block engine and 400 turbo tranny. Orange textured shag carpets, wood paneling on the walls, shag and white leather on the ceiling! Whoever bought this in 1980 was one classy guy. Heat and AC work! it has a heater in the back (pictured) that pumps out some serious heat. I have been driving this thing every day for a couple months now and it is a lot of fun, I just need a small pickup truck for work. The whole back end is fiberglass so there is no rust and the windows and screens all seal tightly, not a drafty van. Although the handle to the rear door is broken so there is a 4"x4" opening in the rear door. it does not latch on its own. I had a new ignition put in the van so the keys don't match the front doors. I put a new heater core in it a month ago- have receipts. The tires on it (6) cost me $1200 about 3 months ago so they are still in 95% shape. The brakes are great. the 400 small block provides plenty of power. Could use a re-alignment. Gets a little wobbly around 60mph. but it will do 55mph comfy. Minor rust on the front hood and doors. nothing structurally unsound. All the blinds on the inside are very vintage and in pristine condition. Small oil leak coming from valve cover gasket. it has leaked ever since ive had it but its so minor I did the tires and heater core first. Speedometer and odometer do not work, nor does the cruise control. They all went out at once. It has a clean clear Indiana title, in my name, in hand. No bull, I wont ship. I may trade for a small pickup truck, and would prefer to add cash for the right truck. Also might do partial trades on quality firearms, no revolvers or anything that costs less than 800 dollars.

This would be great for a hunter as there is no extra crap in the van. I have camped in it a couple times- very roomy. If empty you could probably sleep 5 or 6. Electricity is not ran thru the van, there is a fold down futon but no bed. All the windows work. 

Email is best. I check it monday thru friday and most weekends. Thanks for your time.
